The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Friday, November 07, 2003  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	The Mohun Bagan team management has had a change of heart vis--vis Basudeb Mondal, who was ignored for the National Football League a couple of days ago. The experienced midfielders performance will be monitored over two weeks before a decision is taken. In a meeting of the coaches and club officials, it was decided that if Mondal is up to the mark during the NFL preparation, he may be retained.				 																																																	Meanwhile, it was learnt that Bagan are free to recruit foreign players, according to indications from the Fifa. While they signed a contract with Zimbabwean David on Thursday, two Brazilians  Edu and Leonardo  will arrive on November 15 for trials. If both are selected, then Marcos Parreira will be released before the NFL.  IBP won the IBP Merchants'  Cup tennis crown at the South  Club on Thursday. IBP defeated  CESC A 2-0, with Saurav Panja  thrashing Ashish Sen 6-1, 6-1.  Tejbir Singh and Enrico Piper no then downed the Sen and  Prabir Majumdar 6-0, 6-0. In the  losers' plate final, Tata Steel A  beat M.N. Dastur and Co. 2-0. The Bengal U-15 team failed  to garner full points in the Polly  Umrigar Trophy match against  Bihar in Jamshedpur on Thurs day. According to information  received here, Bihar were 136  for seven at stumps on Day III,  after their overnight 18 for two. BRIEF SCORES
 Bihar 108 amp; 136/7. Bengal 191.
